         <div type="translation">
            <ab>" ��� Has been registered in the great register of the annual charge of the - - - and tenth indiction for the ship of (the monastery of) Metanoia through Christophoros, tabellio, the below mentioned quantity of pure public grain together with the freight-costs and the 1 0/0 payments and all expenses. As follows: Phoibammon, son of Papnuthis, 1 art. Thereof Iason, son of N. N., (has paid) half; N. N., son of N. N., (has paid) half. - -</ab>
